               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dǝrsān maḥyawi “The Life-Giving Homily” (fols. 3ra-72ra)
 I-1)
                     Introductory prayer (fol. 3ra-va) 
 I-2) Reading for Monday, Compline
                     (nǝwam) (fols. 3va-15rb) 
 I-3) Reading for Tuesday, Matins (manfaqa lelit)
                     (fols. 15va-25va) 
 I-4) Reading for Wednesday, Lauds (nagh) (fols.
                     25vb-35rb) 
 I-5) Reading for Thursday, Terce (śalastu säʿat) (fols.
                     35va-46vb) 
 I-6) Reading for Friday, Sext (qätr) (fols. 47ra-55vb) 
                     I-7) Reading for Saturday, None (täsaʿtu säʿat) (fols. 55vb-65va) 
 I-8)
                     Reading for Sunday, Vespers (śark) (fols. 65va-72ra) 
 II) Malkǝʾa ʾIyasus
                     “Image of Jesus” (fols. 72ra-76rb) (s. ChRep no. 125)
 
 Additio 1;
                     colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- For the translation of Text I s. O. Raineri, “Omelia del Salvatore
                        (Trattato etiopico sulla passione di Cristo)”, Orientalia Christiana
                        Periodica 77, 2011,<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ES93151">93-151</ref>.</note>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#72ra">72ra</locus>: ይትባረክ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ ጽሒፈ፡ ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡
                        ለኃጥእ፡ ገብሩ፡ ወልደ፡ አረጋዊ፡ ወተፈጸመ፡ በ፲ወ፱፻፲ወ፫፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ በዘመነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ በወርኀ፡ ኅዳር።
                        According to the colophon the Ms. was written by Walda ʾAragāwi who completed
                        the work in the month of Ḫǝdār in 1913 year of mercy, in the year of John the
                        Evangelist (= 1920 A.D.). </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
